  "description": "<i>Little League Baseball 2002</i> is a baseball game carrying the Little League Baseball license of the organization that organizes local youth baseball and softball leagues throughout the United States and the rest of the world.<br><br>Different teams are available each with different statistics based on batting, fielding and pitching. Game options include a difficulty level selection, adjusting the amount of innings and a selection of different fields. Before the start of the game the batting order can be determined.<br><br>During the batting phase a behind view is used when swinging with an orange circle that can be moved around green cross-hairs to strike at the right time. When pitching the same perspective is used with a red dot moved around the green cross-hairs, a separate bar for pitching power and four options for the pitch type. During field play the perspective shifts to a bird's-eye view.",
